<body>
  <stat-block>
    <creature-heading>
      <h1>Silis, The Old (Plumed Basilisk)</h1>
      <h2>Large Beast, Neutral</h2>
    </creature-heading>

    <top-stats>
      <property-line>
        <h4>Armor Class</h4>
        <p>16 (natural armor)</p>
      </property-line>
      <property-line>
        <h4>Hit Points</h4>
        <p>68</p>
      </property-line>
      <property-line>
        <h4>Speed</h4>
        <p>35ft land/swim</p>
      </property-line>

      <abilities-block data-str="14"
                       data-dex="8"
                       data-con="13"
                       data-int="16"
                       data-wis="16"
                       data-cha="10"></abilities-block>

      <property-line>
        <h4>Damage Immunities</h4>
        <p>poison, psychic</p>
      </property-line>
      <property-line>
        <h4>Condition Immunities</h4>
        <p>poisoned</p>
      </property-line>
      <property-line>
        <h4>Senses</h4>
        <p>blindsight 60 ft. (blind beyond this radius), passive Perception 12</p>
      </property-line>
      <property-line>
        <h4>Languages</h4>
        <p>Common, Elvish, Dwarven, Draconic, telepathy 100 ft</p>
      </property-line>
      <property-line>
        <h4>Challenge</h4>
        <p>4</p>
      </property-line>
    </top-stats>

    <property-block>
      <h4>Terrifying Gaze.</h4>
      <p>If a creature is within 30 feet of the basilisk and the two can see each other, the basilisk
         can force the creature to make a DC 12 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, the creature
         becomes paralyzed. It must repeat the throw at the end of it's next turn. On a success, the effect ends.</p>
        <p> A creature that isn't surprised can avert it's eyes to avoid the saving throw at the start of it's turn.
            If it does so, it can't see the basilisk until the start of it's turn.</p>
    </property-block>
      
    <property-block>
      <h4>Shielded Mind.</h4>
      <p> The basilisk is immune to scrying and to any effect that would sense its emotions.read its
        thoughts or detect its location.</p>
    </property-block>

    <h3>Actions</h3>

    <property-block>
      <h4>Multiattack.</h4>
      <p>The basilisk can attack with its bite attack after a successful constrict attack.</p>
    </property-block>

    <property-block>
      <h4>Bite.</h4>
      <p><i>Melee Weapon Attack:</i> +5 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target.
        <i>Hit:</i>(2d6 + 1) piercinging damage.</p>
    </property-block>
      
      <property-block>
      <h4>Constrict.</h4>
      <p><i>Melee Weapon Attack:</i> +6 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target.
          <i>Hit:</i>(1d8 + 2) piercinging damage, and the target is <i>Grappled</i>. It can free itse;f with a
          DC 16 strength check. Untill the grapple ends, the creature is restrained.</p>
    </property-block>
      
  </stat-block>
